2F30%2F25%29&utm_content=3DThe+Best+%26+The+Brightest+-+SUBSCRIBERS+%281%2F=
30%2F25%29&utm_medium=3Demail_action&utm_source=3Dcustomer.io&utm_term=3Df6=
c60617da42abd12a ) that the maneuver was =E2=80=9CNOT a rescission of the f=
ederal funding freeze.=E2=80=9D K Street, and the rest of America, were lef=
t to scratch their heads.=C2=A0

To help clarify matters, I spoke
to lobbyist Shanti Stanton, the founder of Oxford Strategies and a former P=
elosi staffer, on my podcast, Somebody=E2=80=99s Gotta Win. This excerpt of=
 our full conversation has been lightly edited.

=E2=80=9COh,
Never Mind, You=E2=80=99re Not Getting Your Money=E2=80=9D
----------------------------------------------

Tara Palmeri: It=E2=80=99s Trump=E2=80=99s second go-around, and yet
he and his team still don=E2=80=99t seem to get how Washington works. (The =
chaotic implementation reminded me of the so-called Muslim ban.) You unders=
tand the appropriations process and try to make sure your clients benefit f=
rom it. What do you make of what happened yesterday?=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Shanti Stanton: I=E2=80=99m a very well-established Democratic lobbyist, bu=
t I understand the complaints that Republicans
have about the government being too big, and the need to get more specifics=
 about who=E2=80=99s working there, and what they=E2=80=99re doing. Is ther=
e redundant work? Are there redundant programs? Yes, but there=E2=80=99s be=
en a process in place for over 200 years, and just because Trump was electe=
d president doesn=E2=80=99t mean that he gets to rewrite the Constitution a=
nd erase everything that happened before he became president.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

What did your Republican lobbyist friends think of the freeze?

=C2=A0

I=E2=80=99m in group texts, and oddly, yesterday, I didn=E2=80=99t hear a l=
ot from the Republicans I share clients with=E2=80=94probably because it=E2=
=80=99s easy for me to criticize the administration. I don=E2=80=99t think =
there was anything for them to say. It was so shocking, I think, to all of =
us. And both sides are trying to help our clients navigate this. I
have clients in the nonprofit space, and they have grantees who weren=E2=80=
=99t able to access the accounts they needed to pay their employees and con=
tinue with the programs they=E2=80=99ve been approved to run.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Say more about how your clients were impacted by the freeze.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

When companies get the funding,
or they get a loan, they plan around it. I have a client in the energy spac=
e, and they have a loan, and part of that loan will be used to build a manu=
facturing plant in the U.S. They hire people and they break ground because =
they=E2=80=99re depending on what=E2=80=99s been guaranteed to them. Someti=
mes it=E2=80=99s a corporation, sometimes it=E2=80=99s a school that=E2=80=
=99s hired new teachers, because they have new students, and everyone plans=
 a budget, generally speaking. And these people plan a year in advance. To =
come at
them at the end, and say, =E2=80=9COh, never mind, you=E2=80=99re not getti=
ng your money,=E2=80=9D doesn=E2=80=99t make any sense to me.

The memo said there would be a freeze on all loans and grants for programs =
that don=E2=80=99t reflect Trump=E2=80=99s worldview=E2=80=94so ostensibly,=
 it was designed to hurt programs that benefit Democrats. Is that what happ=
ened?=C2=A0

There=E2=80=99s this widespread notion that poor people are Democrats. That=
 might be true in
Palm Beach, but that=E2=80=99s not true in rural America. Republican member=
s vote for these programs as well, because, depending on their district, th=
ey have a lot of people who benefit from them. I=E2=80=99m from very rural =
Colfax, Washington=E2=80=94try to find that on a map! They=E2=80=99re all R=
epublicans out there. And I promise you that many, many of them are recipie=
nts for some of these programs, whether it=E2=80=99s school lunches or Meal=
s on Wheels. They don=E2=80=99t realize that it=E2=80=99s the government gi=
ving them the money
for that.=C2=A0

