The money that Trump froze came from a budget agreed upon last year, when
Republicans were in power in Congress and Mike Johnson was speaker. Why wou=
ld he freeze it?

=C2=A0

All day I was thinking, where are the Republican appropriators? Appropriato=
rs are very territorial over their space. They work very well together on a=
 bipartisan basis, and they come up with deals and they fund the entire gov=
ernment. It=E2=80=99s their job, and they take it very seriously.=C2=A0

=C2=A0

I was working last year on gun violence research, which, you might expect, =
is more of a Democratic priority than a Republican one, but it does have bi=
partisan support. But with the House being run by Republicans, it wasn=E2=
=80=99t a priority for them. So it didn=E2=80=99t pass in the House bill, a=
nd I thought, I=E2=80=99ll just call the champion on the Appropriations Com=
mittee and see if she=E2=80=99s willing to call over to Health and Human
Services, or the Centers for Disease Control, or Biden, and just see if the=
y can take the money from a different budget, move it over. Even though thi=
s was one of her biggest priorities, she said, =E2=80=9CNo, as an appropria=
tor, we don=E2=80=99t promote spending any money separate from how we have =
specifically laid it out.=E2=80=9D She said, =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m going to =
try to work with the Senate and see if they=E2=80=99ll put it in their bill=
=2E=E2=80=9D But she was unwilling to even=
 think about pushing money from som=
ewhere that wasn=E2=80=99t
specifically a line item.

=C2=A0

Trump has argued that, as president, he has authority to withhold congressi=
onally approved spending that he considers wasteful. He=E2=80=99s talking a=
bout =E2=80=9Cimpoundment,=E2=80=9D which Congress prohibited in 1974, afte=
r Nixon tried the same thing, even forcing recipients, including individual=
 states and localities, to sue for the funds. Do you think this funding fre=
eze could open the door
to a court repealing the Impoundment Control Act, granting Trump power to o=
verride Congress on spending?

Based on the Constitution, this is not something that he=E2=80=99s allowed =
to do. I think it was just about ignorance, because there are so many oppor=
tunities coming up where he can actually cut spending. Why didn=E2=80=99t h=
e just send a letter to agencies saying, =E2=80=9CPlease give me an account=
ing of where
your money=E2=80=99s going, and what employees you have, and who=E2=80=99s =
working one day a week, or five days a week=E2=80=9D? And then as he prepar=
es his budget, he can propose the cuts wherever he wants.

Do you think that Trump is trying to disrupt the balance of power between t=
he White House and Congress? To show Congress that the Office of Management=
 and Budget is more powerful than they are?=C2=A0

=C2=A0

Can I use the word dictatorship? It kind of felt like we were in Russia yes=
terday. The problem is there are still laws in place, and there=E2=80=99s o=
nly so much you can do. He really only controls one of the three branches o=
f government, and he=E2=80=99s got a lot of support in the other two. But h=
