x;"><strong><em>Tara Palmeri: </em></strong><strong>It=E2=80=99s Trump=E2=
=80=99s second go-around, and yet
he and his team still don=E2=80=99t seem to get how Washington works. (The =
chaotic implementation reminded me of the so-called Muslim ban.) You unders=
tand the appropriations process and try to make sure your clients benefit f=
rom it. What do you make of what happened yesterday?=C2=A0</strong></p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;"><em>Shanti Stanton: </em>I=E2=80=99m a very well-established D=
emocratic lobbyist, but I understand the complaints that Republicans
have about the government being too big, and the need to get more specifics=
 about who=E2=80=99s working there, and what they=E2=80=99re doing. Is ther=
e redundant work? Are there redundant programs? Yes, but there=E2=80=99s be=
en a process in place for over 200 years, and just because Trump was electe=
d president doesn=E2=80=99t mean that he gets to rewrite the Constitution a=
nd erase everything that happened before he became president.=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;">
<strong>What did your Republican lobbyist friends think of the freeze?</str=
ong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"marg=
in:0;margin-bottom:0px;">I=E2=80=99m in group texts, and oddly, yesterday, =
I didn=E2=80=99t hear a lot from the Republicans I share clients with=E2=80=
=94probably because it=E2=80=99s easy for me to criticize the administratio=
n. I don=E2=80=99t think there was anything for them to say. It was so shoc=
king, I think, to all of us. And both sides are trying to help our clients =
navigate this. I
have clients in the nonprofit space, and they have grantees who weren=E2=80=
=99t able to access the accounts they needed to pay their employees and con=
tinue with the programs they=E2=80=99ve been approved to run.=C2=A0</p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-=
bottom:0px;"><strong>Say more about how your clients were impacted by the f=
reeze.=C2=A0</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p=
><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">When companies get the funding,
or they get a loan, they plan around it. I have a client in the energy spac=
e, and they have a loan, and part of that loan will be used to build a manu=
facturing plant in the U.S. They hire people and they break ground because =
they=E2=80=99re depending on what=E2=80=99s been guaranteed to them. Someti=
mes it=E2=80=99s a corporation, sometimes it=E2=80=99s a school that=E2=80=
=99s hired new teachers, because they have new students, and everyone plans=
 a budget, generally speaking. And these people plan <em>a year</em> in adv=
ance. To come at
them at the end, and say, =E2=80=9COh, never mind, you=E2=80=99re not getti=
ng your money,=E2=80=9D doesn=E2=80=99t make any sense to me.<br/><br/></p>=
<p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>The memo said there would =
be a freeze on all loans and grants for programs that don=E2=80=99t reflect=
 Trump=E2=80=99s worldview=E2=80=94so ostensibly, it was designed to hurt p=
rograms that benefit Democrats. Is that what happened?</strong>=C2=A0</p><p=
 style=3D"margin:0;"><br/>There=E2=80=99s this widespread notion that poor =
people are Democrats. That might be true in
Palm Beach, but that=E2=80=99s not true in rural America. Republican member=
s vote for these programs as well, because, depending on their district, th=
ey have a lot of people who benefit from them. I=E2=80=99m from very rural =
Colfax, Washington=E2=80=94try to find that on a map! They=E2=80=99re all R=
epublicans out there. And I promise you that many, <em>many</em> of them ar=
e recipients for some of these programs, whether it=E2=80=99s school lunche=
s or Meals on Wheels. They don=E2=80=99t realize that it=E2=80=99s the gove=
rnment giving them the money
for that.=C2=A0</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
