9999997px;"><strong>Nixon
Redux</strong></h3>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
<table width=3D"100%" border=3D"0" cellpadding=3D"0" cellspacing=3D"0" role=
=3D"presentation" style=3D"mso-table-lspace:0pt;mso-table-rspace:0pt;word-b=
reak:break-word;"><tbody><tr><td style=3D"padding-bottom:32px;"><div style=
=3D"color:#000000;direction:ltr;font-family:&#39;Inter&#39;,&#39;Arial&#39;=
;font-size:17px;font-weight:400;letter-spacing:0px;line-height:150%;text-al=
ign:left;mso-line-height-alt:25.5px;"><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0p=
x;"><strong>The money that Trump froze came from a budget agreed upon last =
year, when
Republicans were in power in Congress and Mike Johnson was speaker. Why wou=
ld he freeze it?</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">All day I was thinking, <em=
>where</em> are the Republican appropriators? Appropriators are very territ=
orial over their space. They work very well together on a bipartisan basis,=
 and they come up with deals and they fund the entire government. It=E2=80=
=99s their job, and they take it very seriously.=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margi=
n:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
I was working last year on gun violence research, which, you might expect, =
is more of a Democratic priority than a Republican one, but it does have bi=
partisan support. But with the House being run by Republicans, it wasn=E2=
=80=99t a priority for them. So it didn=E2=80=99t pass in the House bill, a=
nd I thought, I=E2=80=99ll just call the champion on the Appropriations Com=
mittee and see if she=E2=80=99s willing to call over to Health and Human
Services, or the Centers for Disease Control, or Biden, and just see if the=
y can take the money from a different budget, move it over. Even though thi=
s was one of her biggest priorities, she said, =E2=80=9CNo, as an appropria=
tor, we don=E2=80=99t promote spending any money separate from how we have =
specifically laid it out.=E2=80=9D She said, =E2=80=9CI=E2=80=99m going to =
try to work with the Senate and see if they=E2=80=99ll put it in their bill=
=2E=E2=80=9D But she was unwilling to even=
 <em>think</em> about pushing money=
 from somewhere that wasn=E2=80=99t
specifically a line item.</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=C2=
=A0</p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Trump has argued th=
at, as president, he has authority to withhold congressionally approved spe=
nding that he considers wasteful. He=E2=80=99s talking about =E2=80=9Cimpou=
ndment,=E2=80=9D which Congress prohibited in 1974, after Nixon tried the s=
ame thing, even forcing recipients, including individual states and localit=
ies, to sue for the funds. Do you think this funding freeze could open the =
door
to a court </strong><strong><em>repealing</em></strong><strong> the Impound=
ment Control Act, granting Trump power to override Congress on spending?</s=
trong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><br/>Based on the Consti=
tution, this is not something that he=E2=80=99s allowed to do. I think it w=
as just about ignorance, because there are so many opportunities coming up =
where he <em>can</em> actually cut spending. Why didn=E2=80=99t he just sen=
d a letter to agencies saying, =E2=80=9CPlease give me an accounting of whe=
re
your money=E2=80=99s going, and what employees you have, and who=E2=80=99s =
working one day a week, or five days a week=E2=80=9D? And then as he prepar=
es his budget, he can propose the cuts wherever he wants.<br/><br/></p><p s=
tyle=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;"><strong>Do you think that Trump is try=
ing to disrupt the balance of power between the White House and Congress? T=
o show Congress that the Office of Management and Budget is more powerful t=
han they are?=C2=A0</strong></p><p style=3D"margin:0;margin-bottom:0px;">=
=C2=A0</p>
<p style=3D"margin:0;">Can I use the word dictatorship? It kind of felt lik=
e we were in Russia yesterday. The problem is there are still laws in place=
, and there=E2=80=99s only so much you can do. He really only controls one =
of the three branches of government, and he=E2=80=99s got a lot of support =
in the other two. But he still has to follow the rules, and a lot of this s=
tuff still has to happen in the House and the Senate.</p></div>
</td></tr></tbody></table>
